      • conflict

        public IntLLStringSet conflict(IntLLStringSet other,
                               int k)
        Calculates and returns the conflict set of this object and the specified other object. That is - the set of strings belonging to one of the two sets for which a "match" exists in the other set. Here a match is defined as a string of the same length which coincide with the string under consideration up to position k-1.
        Parameters:
        other - the second argument of the operation
        Returns:
        the conflict set

      • conflict

        public IntLLStringSet conflict(IntLLStringSet other)
        Calculates and returns the conflict set of this object and the specified other object. That is - the set of strings belonging to one of the two sets which are prefixes of some string in the other set.
        Parameters:
        other - the second argument of the operation
        Returns:
        the conflict set

      • isLE

        public boolean isLE(IntLLStringSet other)
        Tests whether this set is less than or equal in relation to another set. The definition of the partial ordering relation being tested is: X <= Y if and only if every string in X is a prefix of some string in Y.
        Parameters:
        other - the set against which this one is tested
        Returns:
        true if the ordering relation holds; otherwise false
